    Common Literature
  Venues    
         
    Many journals and
  conferences in the areas of Human-Computer Interaction (HCI) and Computer-Supported
  Cooperative Work (CSCW) publish research in Ubiquitous Computing. Below are
  some specialty venues.    
         
    Specialty Journals    
         
   Personal and Ubiquitous Computing, Springer- Verlag  
   Pervasive and Mobile Computing, Elsevier 
       
    General Journals    
       
   Computer-Supported Cooperative Work,  Kluwer  
   The International Journal of Human-Computer Studies,
  Elsevier 
   Communications of the ACM, ACM 
   IEEE Computer, IEEE 
       
    Specialty
  Conferences    
       
   International Conference on Ubiquitous Computing ( Ubicomp ) 
   IEEE International Conference Pervasive Computing and
  Communications ( PerCom ) 
   IEEE Pervasive Computing, Mobile and Ubiquitous Systems 
       
    General Conferences    
       
   Conference on Human Factors and Computing Systems (CHI) 
   ACM Conference on Computer Supported Cooperative Work
  (CSCW) 
   European Conference of Computer-Supported Cooperative Work
  (ECSCW) 
       
       
   
   
       
   
    
         
   
   
    Some Sources for
  Lecture    
         
    I will draw class
  material from many sources including the following:    
       
   Dourish, P.  Where
  the Action Is: The Foundations of Embodied Interaction,  The MIT Press,
  2001. 
       
    Lakoff , G.  Women, Fire, and Dangerous Things: What Categories Reveal about the
  Mind,  The University
   of Chicago Press, 1987. 
       
    Lakoff , G., Johnson, M.  Philosophy in the Flesh: The Embodied Mind
  and its Challenge to Western Thought,  Basic Books, 1999. 
       
   Norman, D.  The
  Psychology of Everyday Things,  Basic Books, New York, 1988. 
       
       Sch�n, D.  The
  Reflective Practitioner: How Professionals Think in Action,  Basic Books,
  1983.   
           
     Simon, H.  The
  Sciences of the Artificial, Second Edition,  The MIT Press, 1981.   
       
   Nardi, B., Ed.  Context
  and Consciousness: Activity Theory and Human-Computer Interaction,  The
  MIT Press, 1996. 
       
    Winograd , T., Flores, F.,  Understanding Computers and Cognition: A
  New Foundation for Design,  Addison Wesley, 1988. 
         
         
   
   
       
   
    
         
   
   
       
   
   
       
   
    
         
   
   
       
   
   
       
   
    
         
   
   
       
   
   
       
   
        

     

     

 

